Manchester United will play Nottingham Forest in the Carabao Cup semi-final, while Newcastle United will face Southampton. United secured their place in the final four of the competition with a comfortable 3-0 victory over Charlton Athletic at Old Trafford on Tuesday evening. Nottingham Forest had United’s on-loan goalkeeper Dean Henderson to thank for their spot in the semi final as his heroics in the penalty shootout helped dump Wolves out of the competition on Wednesday night. Southampton, meanwhile, knocked out eight-time Carabao Cup winners Manchester City with an impressive 2-0 win against the Premier League champions at St Mary’s. Newcastle United are looking to end their 68-year trophy drought and moved a step closer to winning the Carabao Cup by knocking out Leicester City with a 2-0 victory at St James’ Park on Tuesday. The first leg of the semi finals are scheduled to place in the week commencing January 23, while the return fixtures will be played in the week commencing January 30. For more stories like this, check our sport page. Follow Metro Sport for the latest news on 
Facebook, Twitter and Instagram. 